item.title: About
item.description: About Me I am a 4th year PhD student in Computer Science Department at CMU, and am advised by Weina Wang. Broadly-speaking, I’m interested in queueing theory and stochastic analysis. Right now, I’m a visiting student at the Simons Institute. Research Interest Publications W. Wang, A. Gupta, J.Williams: Probing to minimize
